OL,7,FOne in four deaths of people with
OL,8,Fsevere or profound and multiple
OL,9,Flearning disabilities between 2021-
OL,10,F2023 were treatable, meaning they
OL,11,Fwould have lived if they had received
OL,12,Fbetter care. That's compared to 1 in
OL,13,F13 treatable deaths in the general
OL,14,Fpopulation.
OL,16,FThe average age at which a learning
OL,17,Fdisabled person dies remains unchanged
OL,18,Fbetween the two reports, at 62.5. The
OL,19,Faverage age in the general population
OL,20,Fis 82.
