OL,7,FResponding to the publication of the
OL,8,Fcorrected LeDeR report, Jon Sparkes
OL,9,FOBE, Chief Executive of Mencap, said
OL,10,Fthe handling of such vital and
OL,11,Fsensitive information by the
OL,12,Fgovernment and NHS England needs to
OL,13,Fimprove.
OL,15,F"The LeDeR programme exists because
OL,16,Fpeople with a learning disability and
OL,17,Fautistic people are dying far too
OL,18,Fyoung, often in circumstances that
OL,19,Fcould and should have been prevented.
