OL,7,F"There is no excuse for failing to
OL,8,Fsupport people with a learning
OL,9,Fdisability to access lifesaving
OL,10,Fcancer screening and timely diagnosis.
OL,11,FAnd you simply cannot die from Down
OL,12,Fsyndrome, so questions must be asked
OL,13,Fabout why this is being recorded as an
OL,14,F'unavoidable' cause of death. There
OL,15,Fwould be outrage if other
OL,16,Fcharacteristics were used in this way.
OL,17,FThis hides the real reasons people
OL,18,Fdied, such as missed screening, late
OL,19,Fdiagnosis or failures in basic care."
OL,26,@oD@AOU
