OL,7,F"The updated analysis reaffirms that
OL,8,Fpeople with a learning disability
OL,9,Fcontinue to experience significant
OL,10,Fhealth inequalities: on average, they
OL,11,Fdie 19.5 years younger than the
OL,12,Fgeneral population and are almost
OL,13,Ftwice as likely to die from an
OL,14,Favoidable cause of death," said Dr
OL,15,FZubir.
OL,17,F"This remains unacceptable, and
OL,18,Ftackling these disparities continues
OL,19,Fto be a priority for this government."
